      "description": "This 1997 E36 M3 features the venerable S52 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through a crisp ZF 5-speed manual and a factory 3.15 limited-slip differential. Mechanically robust, it boasts a comprehensive cooling system overhaul including an aluminum radiator and a recently serviced VANOS unit for optimal variable valve timing performance. The suspension geometry is enhanced with Bilstein B8 dampers and H&R sport springs, while the rear subframe has been reinforced to mitigate common chassis fatigue. Recent fluid analysis confirms excellent internal engine health, making this a technically sound, driver-focused machine.",
